&lt;p&gt;Points: 3&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 0&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48300969</guid><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 21:26:58 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Show HN: VAEN – Package and import portable AI coding-agent Harnesses</title><link>https://github.com/sjhalani7/vaen</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Hi HN, I built VAEN (an open source CLI) because I kept running into a boring problem with AI coding-agent workflows: the setup becomes useful, but then it is hard to move.&lt;p&gt;A good, useful agentic harness consists of more than just instructions: skills, mcp servers and more. There should be a better way to share those than just .MD files, and that is why I created VAEN.&lt;p&gt;What works: create a yaml, run the CLI commands as per the repo, and get a .agent file that you can share and extract. 
Think of how awesome it could be if anyone could use a very useful agentic harness, and share it with one CLI command.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Comments URL: &lt;a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48300485"&gt;https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48300485&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Points: 4&lt;/p&gt;
